article.headline: South Alabama 89, North Texas 67
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Demetric Bennett scored 21 points, including three 3-pointers, to help lead South Alabama to an 89-67 win over North Texas on Saturday night. Bennett had a team-high seven rebounds, and Chey Christie added 17 points for the Jaguars (14-5, 5-2 Sun Belt). North Texas, which trailed 48-37 at halftime, faltered in the second half, hitting only about 34 percent of its field goals compared to South Alabama's 62 percent. Kendrick Davis scored 17 points, and Harold Edwards added 13 and had a team-high seven rebounds for the Mean Green (12-7, 5-3). Lionel Brown scored 12 points, including three 3-pointers.
